<ns252:section xmlns:ns252="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.awk.typicalApplications">

  <ns253:title xmlns:ns253="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Typical applications of <ns254:command xmlns:ns254="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">awk</ns254:command></ns253:title>
  <ns255:para xmlns:ns255="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns256:command xmlns:ns256="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Awk</ns256:command> can be used for a very wide range of information 
    processing tasks. Some of the areas where <ns257:command xmlns:ns257="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">awk</ns257:command> is
    particularly useful for are
    <ns258:itemizedlist xmlns:ns258="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns259:listitem xmlns:ns259="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns260:para xmlns:ns260="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">report generation and general text information rendering,</ns260:para></ns259:listitem>
      <ns261:listitem xmlns:ns261="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns262:para xmlns:ns262="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">data validation and</ns262:para></ns261:listitem>
      <ns263:listitem xmlns:ns263="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns264:para xmlns:ns264="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">data transformation.</ns264:para></ns263:listitem>
    </ns258:itemizedlist>
  </ns255:para>
  <ns265:para xmlns:ns265="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    In many ways <ns266:command xmlns:ns266="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">awk</ns266:command> does for text data what <ns267:command xmlns:ns267="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">XSLT</ns267:command>
    does for <ns268:command xmlns:ns268="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">XML</ns268:command>.
  </ns265:para>
  
  <ns269:section xmlns:ns269="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns270:title xmlns:ns270="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Report generation with <ns271:command xmlns:ns271="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">awk</ns271:command></ns270:title>
    <ns272:para xmlns:ns272="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Here awk is used to
      <ns273:itemizedlist xmlns:ns273="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns274:listitem xmlns:ns274="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns275:para xmlns:ns275="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">extract selective information,</ns275:para></ns274:listitem>
        <ns276:listitem xmlns:ns276="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns277:para xmlns:ns277="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">re-order the information into some desired from,</ns277:para></ns276:listitem>
        <ns278:listitem xmlns:ns278="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns279:para xmlns:ns279="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">format fields and</ns279:para></ns278:listitem>
        <ns280:listitem xmlns:ns280="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns281:para xmlns:ns281="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          perform some basic data processing tasks like summing up certain fields or
          other basic mathematical or textual processing tasks.
        </ns281:para></ns280:listitem>
      </ns273:itemizedlist>
    </ns272:para>
  </ns269:section>

  <ns282:section xmlns:ns282="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns283:title xmlns:ns283="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Data validation</ns283:title>
    <ns284:para xmlns:ns284="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns285:command xmlns:ns285="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Awk</ns285:command> can be used to verify that data received is in a valid
      form for processing by other applications. For example, it can be used to verify that 
      <ns286:itemizedlist xmlns:ns286="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns287:listitem xmlns:ns287="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns288:para xmlns:ns288="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          the required fields are present,
        </ns288:para></ns287:listitem>
        <ns289:listitem xmlns:ns289="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns290:para xmlns:ns290="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          that fields have the correct format (<ns291:abbrev xmlns:ns291="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">e.g.</ns291:abbrev> that they are purely 
          numeric or that they are within a specified range),
        </ns290:para></ns289:listitem>
        <ns292:listitem xmlns:ns292="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns293:para xmlns:ns293="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          that the file has the required number of records,
        </ns293:para></ns292:listitem>
      </ns286:itemizedlist>
      and so on.
    </ns284:para>
  </ns282:section>
  
  <ns294:section xmlns:ns294="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns295:title xmlns:ns295="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Data transformation</ns295:title>
    <ns296:para xmlns:ns296="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      At times you may need to transform the output of one application into a form
      which makes it suitable as input for another. If the format of both, the source 
      and the target information is text, the <ns297:command xmlns:ns297="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">awk</ns297:command> may provide
      a very fast mechanism for defining such a transformation in the same way as what
      <ns298:command xmlns:ns298="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">XSLT</ns298:command> does for <ns299:command xmlns:ns299="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">XML data</ns299:command>.
    </ns296:para>
  </ns294:section>
</ns252:section>